01:02.176 --> 01:04.724
I shall sew it on for you, my little man.

01:04.751 --> 01:06.117
It may hurt a little.

01:06.348 --> 01:07.759
What's your name?

01:07.974 --> 01:09.932
Wendy Moira Angela Darling.

01:10.185 --> 01:12.094
- What's yours?
- Peter Pan.

01:12.687 --> 01:14.596
Watch your daughter.
She's wonderful.

01:14.814 --> 01:16.688
She's stealing the show.

01:17.525 --> 01:19.980
I think it's perfectly sweet of you.

01:20.194 --> 01:21.024
Louder!

01:21.237 --> 01:24.652
I think it's perfectly sweet of you.

01:24.907 --> 01:28.573
I shall give you a kiss if you like.

01:29.704 --> 01:31.696
Don't you know what a kiss is?

01:31.914 --> 01:34.405
I shall, once you give one to me.

01:40.631 --> 01:42.338
Now I shall give you a kiss.

01:50.849 --> 01:53.969
I don't ever wanna become a man.

01:55.687 --> 01:58.392
I always wanna be a little boy and have fun.

02:01.192 --> 02:03.905
<i>We wanna be like Peter Pan.</i>

02:03.931 --> 02:06.342
<i>We don't wanna grow up</i>

02:09.658 --> 02:10.904
Brad.

02:12.787 --> 02:14.661
Yeah, I'm at my daughter's play.

02:19.752 --> 02:20.725
It's impossible.

02:20.751 --> 02:24.154
I'm on a plane to London tomorrow night with my family.

02:24.339 --> 02:28.040
A children's hospital is dedicating an entire wing to Granny Wendy.

02:28.428 --> 02:29.257
Brad...

02:29.470 --> 02:31.379
Peter, you're missing it.

02:31.597 --> 02:34.882
All right. I want a meeting, tomorrow a.m.

02:35.100 --> 02:36.505
Dad, my game!

02:36.531 --> 02:38.043
You promised.

02:38.270 --> 02:40.144
Listen, it's my son's big game.

02:40.397 --> 02:42.527
Last game of the season. Santa Series.

02:42.553 --> 02:44.289
I gotta be there.
I promised.

02:45.318 --> 02:46.516
We'll make it short.

02:47.028 --> 02:49.318
I'll be there. My word is my bond.

02:49.573 --> 02:50.784
<i>We never, never, never</i>

02:50.810 --> 02:52.350
<i>Never, never, never, never</i>

02:52.576 --> 02:55.991
<i>Never, never, ever wanna grow up</i>

02:56.871 --> 02:58.663
Strike three! You're out.

03:03.544 --> 03:05.702
Bluejays, come on!

03:05.921 --> 03:09.088
Jack! Come on, Bluejays!

03:09.300 --> 03:10.296
Bluejays!

03:12.387 --> 03:13.667
Fire it up!

03:17.516 --> 03:18.965
Where is your father?

03:18.991 --> 03:20.163
He's missing it.

03:20.394 --> 03:23.679
Daddy'll be here. He promised.

03:24.064 --> 03:25.013
Jerry? Jack?

03:25.232 --> 03:26.228
- Jim.
- I said that.

03:26.483 --> 03:28.217
Go to the game ahead of me.

03:28.243 --> 03:29.462
Film what I miss.

03:29.653 --> 03:32.227
This is the speech for your grandmother's tribute.

03:32.448 --> 03:33.313
- On cards?
- Yes.

03:33.532 --> 03:35.525
- Number those. Who wrote it?
- Ned Miller.

03:35.743 --> 03:37.450
I loved his annual report.
Read it.

03:37.661 --> 03:42.323
"For the past 70 years, the Granny Wendy we honor tonight...

03:42.540 --> 03:45.790
...has given hope and care and life to hundreds of orphans."

03:46.002 --> 03:47.033
Great.

03:47.378 --> 03:49.252
Mommy, where's Daddy?

