59:38.373 --> 59:39.701
But, Peter...

59:39.958 --> 59:41.371
...you've grown up.

59:41.397 --> 59:43.850
You promised never to grow old.

59:48.592 --> 59:50.549
His nose got real big.

59:50.802 --> 59:54.467
Well, welcome back to Never Land, Pan the Man.

59:54.889 --> 59:58.009
Don't listen to that faerie and that brainless fungus!

59:58.267 --> 59:59.640
I got Pan's sword!

59:59.666 --> 01:00:00.961
I'm the Pan now!

01:00:01.187 --> 01:00:05.184
You think this guy's gonna take it from me? Rufio?

01:00:06.859 --> 01:00:10.524
Wait! If Tink believes, maybe he is.

01:00:16.118 --> 01:00:20.945
Are you gonna follow this drooler against <i>Capitan</i> Hook?

01:00:21.623 --> 01:00:24.796
What's he doing here if he's not Peter Pan, huh?

01:00:24.822 --> 01:00:26.440
He don't look happy here.

01:00:26.669 --> 01:00:28.560
And who are them kids Hook's got?

01:00:28.586 --> 01:00:29.732
Give him a chance!

01:00:29.965 --> 01:00:34.294
Those are my kids, and Hook's gonna kill them unless we do something.

01:00:35.637 --> 01:00:38.803
Help me. Please.

01:00:39.474 --> 01:00:40.551
Yeah, come on!

01:00:40.577 --> 01:00:42.037
Give him a chance!

01:00:48.149 --> 01:00:50.556
Well, I should claw myself with my own hook.

01:00:50.777 --> 01:00:54.311
Not to kill Pan when I had the chance!

01:00:54.864 --> 01:00:56.160
What have I done?

01:00:56.186 --> 01:00:58.092
What have I done, Smee?

01:00:58.576 --> 01:01:02.075
Agreed to a preposterous plan, an absurd war.

01:01:02.329 --> 01:01:05.828
Now I'm bound by my indefatigable good form to wait.

01:01:06.083 --> 01:01:07.685
I'll fix you a nice plate.

01:01:07.711 --> 01:01:08.943
Wait for what?

01:01:09.169 --> 01:01:14.294
Whether it be three days or three decades, he'll always be a fat, old Pan.

01:01:14.925 --> 01:01:16.997
I hate being disappointed, Smee.

01:01:17.023 --> 01:01:19.612
And I hate living in this flawed body!

01:01:19.805 --> 01:01:22.212
And I hate living in Never Land!

01:01:22.432 --> 01:01:24.555
And I hate, I hate...

01:01:24.809 --> 01:01:29.138
...I hate Peter Pan!

01:01:31.482 --> 01:01:34.899
Smee? Smee?

01:01:37.072 --> 01:01:39.741
I've just had a sublime vision.

01:01:44.328 --> 01:01:46.570
All the jagged parts of my life...

01:01:46.831 --> 01:01:51.457
...have come together to form a complete and mystical whole.

01:01:53.755 --> 01:01:55.249
An epiphany.

01:01:56.132 --> 01:01:57.377
A "piphy" what?

01:01:58.509 --> 01:02:00.466
My life is over.

01:02:00.678 --> 01:02:01.958
You've lost your appetite?

01:02:02.388 --> 01:02:03.798
Yes.

01:02:04.056 --> 01:02:05.301
Goodbye.

01:02:06.683 --> 01:02:07.697
Where're you going?

01:02:07.723 --> 01:02:09.164
Are you getting dramatic?

01:02:09.352 --> 01:02:10.431
Goodbye, Smee.

01:02:10.687 --> 01:02:13.604
Captain, why don't we play with your island?

01:02:14.148 --> 01:02:17.981
All the little Indians and the soldiers and all the Lost Boys?

01:02:18.236 --> 01:02:20.443
Here we go.

01:02:22.198 --> 01:02:25.283
No stopping me this time, Smee.

01:02:25.535 --> 01:02:26.649
This is it.

01:02:26.869 --> 01:02:30.119
Don't make a move, Smee.
Not a step.

01:02:30.539 --> 01:02:32.363
My finger's on the trigger.

01:02:32.389 --> 01:02:34.348
Don't try to stop me, Smee.

01:02:34.585 --> 01:02:35.784
Oh, not again.

01:02:36.004 --> 01:02:36.834
This is it.

01:02:37.172 --> 01:02:39.626
Don't try to stop me this time, Smee.

01:02:39.652 --> 01:02:42.238
Don't try to stop me this time, Smee.

01:02:42.426 --> 01:02:45.646
Don't you dare try to stop me this time, Smee.

01:02:45.672 --> 01:02:46.698
Try to stop me.

01:02:48.140 --> 01:02:49.954
You better get up off your ass.

01:02:49.980 --> 01:02:50.916
Get over here!

01:02:51.143 --> 01:02:52.601
- I'm coming!
- Stop me!

01:02:52.811 --> 01:02:54.286
This is not a joke!

01:02:54.312 --> 01:02:56.252
I'm committing suicide!

01:03:00.444 --> 01:03:02.602
Don't ever frighten me like that again.

01:03:02.821 --> 01:03:04.648
- Sorry.
- What are you, a sadist?

01:03:04.865 --> 01:03:06.738
I'm sorry. How do you feel now?

01:03:07.367 --> 01:03:09.822
- I want to die.
- Oh, now, now.

01:03:10.036 --> 01:03:11.224
There's no adventure here.

01:03:11.250 --> 01:03:12.848
You call this "no adventure"?

01:03:13.039 --> 01:03:15.281
Death is the only great adventure I have left.

01:03:15.541 --> 01:03:17.119
Let's get you into bed.

01:03:17.335 --> 01:03:18.415
It's all over.

01:03:18.628 --> 01:03:19.490
I'm so tired.

01:03:19.516 --> 01:03:21.903
Don't upset yourself, captain.

01:03:22.132 --> 01:03:24.705
My career is over.

01:03:24.968 --> 01:03:27.838
This was supposed to be the war to end all wars.

01:03:28.095 --> 01:03:29.603
And it will be, captain.

01:03:29.629 --> 01:03:31.074
The ultimate war.

01:03:33.475 --> 01:03:37.224
There must be a way to get at him, to get even with him...

01:03:37.479 --> 01:03:40.185
...to get him where it really would hurt.

01:03:40.399 --> 01:03:44.479
There must be something I haven't thought of. Where is he vulnerable?

01:03:45.321 --> 01:03:48.487
No more talk about doing away with yourself.

01:03:48.740 --> 01:03:52.192
I mean, what would the world be like without Captain Hook?

01:03:52.786 --> 01:03:54.909
Indeed. Good form, Smee.

01:03:55.372 --> 01:03:58.339
What would the world be like without me?

01:03:58.365 --> 01:03:59.774
There you go.

01:04:00.002 --> 01:04:01.828
I'm ready for my nightcap.

01:04:02.087 --> 01:04:04.792
Abso-flogging-lutely.

01:04:05.006 --> 01:04:07.580
I think a bit of skulduggery would do you good.

01:04:07.801 --> 01:04:10.588
Take your mind off this Pan business.

01:04:10.803 --> 01:04:14.801
First thing tomorrow morning, we'll shoot some Indians out at Long Tom.

01:04:15.016 --> 01:04:17.541
I'm tired of killing Indians and Lost Boys.

01:04:17.567 --> 01:04:18.741
I always kill them.

01:04:18.978 --> 01:04:20.542
I want to kill Peter Pan.

01:04:20.568 --> 01:04:21.755
I wanna kill him!

01:04:21.940 --> 01:04:24.513
Hear me? 
I want to kill him.

01:04:24.734 --> 01:04:26.394
Oh, dear.

