<i>Gotta train</i>

01:06:59.550 --> 01:07:01.092
<i>In the rain</i>

01:07:01.343 --> 01:07:02.588
<i>In the sun</i>

01:07:02.845 --> 01:07:04.422
<i>In the snow</i>

01:07:04.638 --> 01:07:06.844
<i>Ten below</i>
<i>Gotta move</i>

01:07:07.057 --> 01:07:08.766
<i>Gotta do</i>
<i>Gotta grow</i>

01:07:10.770 --> 01:07:12.809
Go easy on me. I'm a beginner.

01:07:13.022 --> 01:07:14.220
Low! High! High!

01:07:18.068 --> 01:07:19.269
All right, gramps.

01:07:19.295 --> 01:07:20.963
Give it your best shot.

01:07:21.196 --> 01:07:23.568
Rufio's only trying to help.
Listen. Learn.

01:07:23.949 --> 01:07:24.810
Okay, you ready?

01:07:24.836 --> 01:07:26.180
I don't wanna hurt you.

01:07:30.330 --> 01:07:31.872
Watch your skin!

01:07:32.207 --> 01:07:33.370
Be bangerang, old man.

01:07:46.637 --> 01:07:47.666
What are you doing?

01:07:47.692 --> 01:07:49.912
How does this help me get my kids back?

01:07:50.100 --> 01:07:51.510
What do I have to do next?

01:07:51.768 --> 01:07:56.264
Next, time to fly.

01:08:02.403 --> 01:08:06.021
Just think happy thoughts.

01:08:06.239 --> 01:08:10.189
All you need is one happy thought, Peter, and it'll make you fly.

01:08:11.203 --> 01:08:12.662
I got it!

01:08:13.372 --> 01:08:16.953
Not being in this slingshot would make me very happy!

01:08:18.877 --> 01:08:20.287
He's going up!

01:08:20.545 --> 01:08:22.870
He's coming down!

01:08:26.175 --> 01:08:28.031
Now, pay attention, class.

01:08:28.057 --> 01:08:29.984
We have a lot to go over.

01:08:30.179 --> 01:08:35.008
"Lesson one:
Why parents hate their children."

01:08:37.562 --> 01:08:38.760
Anyone?

01:08:39.606 --> 01:08:41.977
Doesn't Mommy read to us every night?

01:08:42.233 --> 01:08:46.444
You, the cute little urchin in the front row...

01:08:47.112 --> 01:08:50.777
Won't you share your thoughts with the whole class?

01:08:50.991 --> 01:08:51.821
Yes.

01:08:52.033 --> 01:08:54.786
I said Mommy reads to us every night...

01:08:54.996 --> 01:08:57.487
...because she loves us very much.

01:08:57.707 --> 01:08:59.366
Loves you?
Isn't that...

01:09:00.584 --> 01:09:02.707
The "L" word, captain.

01:09:03.545 --> 01:09:04.411
No, child.

01:09:04.630 --> 01:09:09.375
Your mother reads to you every night in order to stupefy you to sleep...

01:09:09.676 --> 01:09:13.673
...so that she and Daddy can sit down for three minutes without you...

01:09:13.930 --> 01:09:19.006
...and your mindless, inexhaustible, unstoppable, repetitive demands:

01:09:19.269 --> 01:09:20.846
"He took my toy."

01:09:21.104 --> 01:09:22.349
"She hid my bear."

01:09:22.604 --> 01:09:24.996
"I want to potty. I want a cookie.

01:09:25.022 --> 01:09:26.497
I want to stay up."

01:09:26.734 --> 01:09:27.787
"I want, I want, I

01:09:27.813 --> 01:09:29.332
want!" "Me, me, me, me!"

01:09:29.528 --> 01:09:31.484
"Mine, mine, mine, mine!"

01:09:31.697 --> 01:09:34.698
"Now, now, now!"

01:09:34.908 --> 01:09:37.743
Can't you understand, child?

01:09:38.203 --> 01:09:40.750
They tell you stories to shut you up.

01:09:40.776 --> 01:09:42.357
And conk you out.

01:09:42.582 --> 01:09:46.201
That's not true, Jack.
You're a liar!

01:09:46.420 --> 01:09:48.792
Lie? Me?

01:09:50.756 --> 01:09:52.335
Never!

01:09:53.260 --> 01:09:56.345
The truth is far too much fun.

01:09:59.058 --> 01:10:04.182
Before you were born, your parents would stay up all night together...

01:10:04.521 --> 01:10:06.099
...just to see the sunrise.

01:10:06.356 --> 01:10:07.435
Don't be frightened.

01:10:07.649 --> 01:10:12.773
Maggie, before you were born, they were happier.

01:10:13.446 --> 01:10:15.189
They were free.

01:10:16.198 --> 01:10:18.904
You are a bad man.

01:10:19.119 --> 01:10:20.910
Smee, flunk the maggot.

01:10:21.204 --> 01:10:22.698
Abso-flogging-lutely.

01:10:22.956 --> 01:10:24.663
An "F"?

01:10:27.376 --> 01:10:29.452
He gave me an "F"!

01:10:31.964 --> 01:10:35.167
Your father went to your sister's school play, did he not?

01:10:35.926 --> 01:10:39.260
But did he go to your baseball game?

01:10:41.932 --> 01:10:43.427
How'd you know about that?

01:10:43.684 --> 01:10:48.227
He missed the most important game on the most important day...

01:10:48.480 --> 01:10:50.722
...of your young life.

01:10:52.526 --> 01:10:54.648
- I wanna tear your hook off!
- Easy.

01:10:54.861 --> 01:10:57.316
I hate, I hate you, Mr. Hook!

01:10:58.114 --> 01:10:59.573
What did I tell you, Smee?

01:10:59.599 --> 01:11:01.224
No little children love me.

01:11:01.451 --> 01:11:02.649
Of course they do.

01:11:02.911 --> 01:11:05.236
Come on.
You're depressing the captain.

01:11:05.455 --> 01:11:06.701
Jack, listen to me!

01:11:06.727 --> 01:11:09.809
Never let him make you forget!
Never forget...

01:11:10.001 --> 01:11:11.376
...Mommy and Daddy!

01:11:11.586 --> 01:11:15.001
Think of a way to run home, Jack!
Run home!

01:11:15.214 --> 01:11:16.412
Run home?

01:11:20.637 --> 01:11:22.428
You are home.

01:11:25.308 --> 01:11:26.470
Right?

01:11:41.699 --> 01:11:43.490
Oh, yeah.

01:12:10.226 --> 01:12:12.681
No, no, no.
We don't use them.

01:12:12.895 --> 01:12:14.221
Why do you have them?

01:12:14.247 --> 01:12:16.455
So we don't have to use them.

01:12:17.233 --> 01:12:19.355
Don't crowd me!

01:12:19.735 --> 01:12:21.145
Come on, Thud Butt!

01:12:33.290 --> 01:12:34.405
Everybody say grace.

01:12:34.625 --> 01:12:35.454
Bless this, Lord...

01:12:35.667 --> 01:12:37.292
Grace!

01:12:46.553 --> 01:12:48.593
All of my favorite Never Foods!

01:12:48.847 --> 01:12:52.844
Yams, mamey apples and banana squash!

01:12:53.184 --> 01:12:57.312
Wash it down, calabash and papaw!

01:13:01.484 --> 01:13:03.143
Can you blow on this?

01:13:04.028 --> 01:13:04.894
Thank you.

01:13:29.803 --> 01:13:31.677
This is good!

01:13:44.525 --> 01:13:46.067
Are you eating that?

01:13:48.363 --> 01:13:50.071
No, please.

01:13:51.074 --> 01:13:52.070
Eat!

01:13:52.450 --> 01:13:53.280
What's the deal?

01:13:53.306 --> 01:13:54.551
Where's the real food?

01:13:54.744 --> 01:13:58.991
If you can't imagine yourself being Peter Pan, you won't be him, so eat up!

01:13:59.206 --> 01:14:00.739
Eat what? There's nothing here.

01:14:00.765 --> 01:14:02.149
Gandhi ate more than this.

01:14:02.334 --> 01:14:04.492
This used to be your favorite game.

01:14:04.711 --> 01:14:05.684
Forget the games.

01:14:05.710 --> 01:14:06.714
I want real food!

01:14:06.740 --> 01:14:07.655
Steak, eggs...

01:14:07.840 --> 01:14:12.585
You can't.
Eat your heart out, you crinkled, wrinkled fat bag!

01:14:12.845 --> 01:14:14.120
You're very ill-mannered...

01:14:14.146 --> 01:14:15.657
You're a slug-eating worm.

01:14:15.848 --> 01:14:17.223
You can do better than that!

01:14:17.599 --> 01:14:18.714
You're encouraging them?

01:14:18.934 --> 01:14:21.206
Show me your fastball, dust brain!

01:14:21.232 --> 01:14:23.704
You paunchy, sag-bottomed puke pot!

01:14:23.938 --> 01:14:25.978
Bangerang, Rufio!

01:14:26.191 --> 01:14:29.109
You're a very poor role model for these kids, you know?

01:14:32.406 --> 01:14:34.445
You don't have a fourth-grade reading level.

01:14:34.658 --> 01:14:35.753
Hemorrhoidal sucknavel.

01:14:35.779 --> 01:14:37.683
Maybe a fifth-grade reading level.

01:14:40.830 --> 01:14:44.281
Oil-dripping, beef-fart sniffing bubble butt.

01:14:46.419 --> 01:14:47.969
Someone has a severe caca mouth.

01:14:47.995 --> 01:14:48.769
You know that?

01:14:48.963 --> 01:14:50.588
You are a fart factory!

01:14:50.840 --> 01:14:54.339
Slug-slime sack of rat guts and cat vomit...

01:14:54.594 --> 01:14:55.792
...cheesy scab...

01:14:56.012 --> 01:14:58.337
...picked pimple-squeezing finger bandage!

01:14:58.556 --> 01:15:03.680
A week-old maggot burger with everything on it and flies on the side!

01:15:05.937 --> 01:15:07.515
Substitute chemistry teacher.

01:15:07.731 --> 01:15:09.937
Come on, Rufio, hit him back.

01:15:10.693 --> 01:15:11.523
Mung tongue!

01:15:12.862 --> 01:15:14.937
- Math tutor.
- Pinhead.

01:15:15.823 --> 01:15:17.198
- Prison barber.
- Mother lover.

01:15:17.407 --> 01:15:18.522
Nearsighted gynecologist.

01:15:18.742 --> 01:15:19.825
In your face, camelcake!

01:15:19.851 --> 01:15:21.340
In your rear, cow derrière!

01:15:21.536 --> 01:15:23.576
Lying, crying, spying, prying ultra-pig!

01:15:23.788 --> 01:15:25.745
Lewd, crude bag of pre-chewed food dude.

01:15:25.957 --> 01:15:27.617
Bangerang, Peter!

01:15:30.628 --> 01:15:33.202
You man! Stupid, stupid man!

01:15:33.423 --> 01:15:36.293
If I'm a maggot burger, why don't you just eat me?

01:15:36.885 --> 01:15:40.716
You zebra-headed, slime-coated, pimple-farming, paramecium brain...

01:15:40.972 --> 01:15:44.720
...munching on your own mucus, suffering from Peter Pan envy!

01:15:44.934 --> 01:15:46.344
What's a "paramecium brain"?

01:15:46.560 --> 01:15:48.374
I'll tell you what a paramecium is!

01:15:48.400 --> 01:15:49.539
That's a paramecium!

01:15:49.730 --> 01:15:53.016
It's a one-celled critter with no brain that can't fly!

01:15:53.276 --> 01:15:54.969
Don't mess with me, man!

01:15:54.995 --> 01:15:56.052
I'm a lawyer!

01:15:56.237 --> 01:15:58.028
Banning, Banning!

01:16:02.951 --> 01:16:05.524
Rufio! Rufio!

01:16:11.626 --> 01:16:15.874
Oh, Rufio, why don't you just go suck on a dead dog's nose?

01:16:24.055 --> 01:16:25.633
You're doing it.

01:16:26.057 --> 01:16:30.006
- Doing what?
- Using your imagination, Peter.

01:16:56.170 --> 01:16:58.965
You're playing with us, Peter.

01:16:58.991 --> 01:17:01.319
You're doing it, Peter.

01:17:22.445 --> 01:17:24.651
Drink your papaw, Peter.

01:17:25.990 --> 01:17:27.568
How is it?

01:17:28.701 --> 01:17:30.076
Bangerang.

01:17:32.246 --> 01:17:33.823
Catch!

01:17:41.589 --> 01:17:42.999
Hey, Pockets...

01:17:43.257 --> 01:17:44.455
...catch!

01:17:45.175 --> 01:17:47.382
Oh, Don't Ask!

01:18:01.316 --> 01:18:03.225
Bangerang!

01:18:11.075 --> 01:18:13.281
Hey, Pan the Man, catch this!

01:18:13.494 --> 01:18:14.609
Peter, look out!

01:18:14.829 --> 01:18:15.694
Peter, watch out!

01:18:48.362 --> 01:18:50.069
Bangerang.

01:19:06.004 --> 01:19:07.462
Peter...

01:19:07.922 --> 01:19:09.796
...can I talk to you?

01:19:10.049 --> 01:19:11.627
Sure, Thud.

01:19:13.135 --> 01:19:15.377
- I remember Tootles.
- You do?

01:19:15.596 --> 01:19:17.138
He was lost too.

01:19:17.973 --> 01:19:19.515
How could you know Tootles?

01:19:19.933 --> 01:19:22.009
He was a Lost Boy.

01:19:22.353 --> 01:19:24.559
These are his marbles.

01:19:26.315 --> 01:19:28.936
These are his happy thoughts.

01:19:36.283 --> 01:19:38.380
He really did lose his marbles.

01:19:38.406 --> 01:19:40.435
Yeah, he lost them good.

01:19:42.789 --> 01:19:44.581
Peter, you know what?

01:19:44.875 --> 01:19:47.710
My happy thought will help you.

01:19:48.712 --> 01:19:50.289
What's your happy thought?

01:19:51.297 --> 01:19:53.539
Mine's my mother.

01:19:54.259 --> 01:19:57.045
Do you remember your mother, Peter?

01:19:57.512 --> 01:19:58.970
Wish I could.

01:20:01.223 --> 01:20:02.967
Listen.

01:20:19.366 --> 01:20:20.694
My mom sang that song.

01:20:20.951 --> 01:20:24.236
My young Jack, tell me about the game of baseball.

01:20:24.496 --> 01:20:25.731
I can't remember.

01:20:25.757 --> 01:20:29.314
Are the mates standing or are they on horseback?

01:20:31.336 --> 01:20:36.212
<i>The stars are all my friends</i>

01:20:36.466 --> 01:20:40.333
<i>Till the nighttime ends</i>

01:20:40.553 --> 01:20:44.420
<i>So I know I'm not alone</i>

01:20:45.016 --> 01:20:48.884
<i>When I'm here on my own</i>

01:20:49.896 --> 01:20:53.763
<i>Isn't that a wonder</i>

01:20:54.525 --> 01:20:57.811
<i>When you're alone</i>

01:20:58.779 --> 01:21:02.397
<i>You're not alone</i>

01:21:02.658 --> 01:21:07.783
<i>Not really alone</i>

01:21:52.165 --> 01:21:55.119
Good night, Never Land!

01:22:33.371 --> 01:22:34.839
What is it? I hear it.

01:22:34.865 --> 01:22:36.065
I hear it again.

01:22:37.625 --> 01:22:40.294
Smee, it's that crocodile, back from the dead!

01:22:41.462 --> 01:22:45.756
Tick-tock, tick-tock, tick-tock, tick-tock, tick-tock!

01:22:45.966 --> 01:22:47.840
Is that the clock?

01:22:50.345 --> 01:22:51.989
You killed that croc years ago.

01:22:52.015 --> 01:22:53.657
We smash every clock we find.

01:22:53.850 --> 01:22:56.056
Little elf didn't know any better.

01:22:58.771 --> 01:23:00.479
To the museum, at once.

01:23:14.411 --> 01:23:19.156
Shine 'em up! Put a fresh coat of varnish on your peg, right here!

01:23:32.553 --> 01:23:34.463
Broken clocks...

01:23:34.723 --> 01:23:39.431
Each one ticked its last tock, and now all is well.

01:23:40.353 --> 01:23:41.728
Just listen.

01:23:41.937 --> 01:23:43.597
I don't hear anything.

01:23:44.023 --> 01:23:47.226
I know! Good form! Exactly!

01:23:47.443 --> 01:23:50.360
Jack, you see this? Come over here.

01:23:50.570 --> 01:23:51.733
You can take it.

01:23:51.947 --> 01:23:54.412
This is Barbecue's very own bedside clock.

01:23:54.438 --> 01:23:56.433
He was quite an infamous pirate.

01:23:56.619 --> 01:24:00.367
I smashed this clock immediately after I gutted him.

01:24:00.581 --> 01:24:02.538
His ship made a pretty bonfire!

01:24:02.791 --> 01:24:05.708
Such a pretty, pretty...

01:24:11.716 --> 01:24:14.919
What is that I hear?

01:24:16.513 --> 01:24:18.007
A ticking?

01:24:20.600 --> 01:24:22.557
Smee, stop the ticking!

01:24:23.311 --> 01:24:26.146
Stop that! Stop that "tick-tick"!

01:24:26.731 --> 01:24:28.020
There's no ticking here.

01:24:28.046 --> 01:24:29.709
There's nothing left to tick.

01:24:31.443 --> 01:24:33.650
Oh, my God!

01:24:34.029 --> 01:24:38.608
This is for the ticking that might have been.

01:24:39.785 --> 01:24:41.577
Get his father's watch!

01:24:44.540 --> 01:24:45.950
Go on.

01:24:46.208 --> 01:24:47.951
You know you want to.

01:24:48.210 --> 01:24:49.918
Give it a try.

01:24:51.004 --> 01:24:52.202
Go on.

01:24:52.464 --> 01:24:54.088
This is for...

01:24:54.758 --> 01:24:57.509
...never letting me blow bubbles in my chocolate milk!

01:24:59.471 --> 01:25:00.901
Good form! Bravo!

01:25:00.927 --> 01:25:03.196
Isn't that wonderful?

01:25:03.391 --> 01:25:06.725
This is for never letting me jump on my own bed!

01:25:07.729 --> 01:25:10.683
Make time stand still, laddie.

01:25:10.898 --> 01:25:14.563
For always making promises and breaking them!

01:25:14.777 --> 01:25:17.019
For never doing anything with me.

01:25:18.615 --> 01:25:21.402
For a father who's never there, Jack?

01:25:24.120 --> 01:25:28.283
Jack, for a father who didn't save you on the ship.

01:25:28.958 --> 01:25:31.034
Who wouldn't save us...

01:25:31.251 --> 01:25:33.410
Who couldn't save you, Jack.

01:25:33.879 --> 01:25:36.833
He wouldn't.
He didn't even try.

01:25:37.090 --> 01:25:41.005
He was there, we were there, and he wouldn't try.

01:25:43.597 --> 01:25:45.424
Jack...

01:25:45.641 --> 01:25:46.886
...he will try.

01:25:48.602 --> 01:25:50.843
And the question will be:

01:25:51.104 --> 01:25:54.639
When the time comes, do you want to be saved?

01:25:56.067 --> 01:25:58.143
Now, don't you answer now.
No, no, no, no.

01:25:58.736 --> 01:26:02.485
Now it's time to be whatever you want to be.

01:26:03.617 --> 01:26:06.072
Put behind you any thoughts of home...

01:26:06.327 --> 01:26:09.114
...that place of broken promises.

01:26:10.164 --> 01:26:11.195
That what?

01:26:12.583 --> 01:26:15.667
Have I ever made a promise, Jack...

01:26:15.920 --> 01:26:19.169
...I have not kept?

01:26:21.843 --> 01:26:23.550
Have I, son?

01:26:51.788 --> 01:26:53.615
Come on. Let's go!

01:27:02.965 --> 01:27:04.128
I don't like this game.

01:27:04.342 --> 01:27:07.343
"Steal Hook's hook As fast as you can."

01:27:07.595 --> 01:27:09.386
"It'll make you proud."

01:27:09.889 --> 01:27:12.676
"Then you crow like Pan."

01:27:12.892 --> 01:27:15.152
Confound it, Druscilla, glove me.

01:27:15.178 --> 01:27:17.163
The game is about to start.

01:27:23.985 --> 01:27:27.153
I need my bubbly.
Give me my bubbly.

01:27:32.035 --> 01:27:34.608
Steal Hook's hook, then crow!

01:27:54.807 --> 01:27:56.385
Jackie, boy! Jack!

01:27:57.268 --> 01:28:00.518
This is for all the games your daddy missed.

01:28:00.729 --> 01:28:03.516
Hook would never miss your game, son.

01:28:03.732 --> 01:28:05.226
You're almost there. Take it.

01:28:05.484 --> 01:28:06.813
What's he looking at?

01:28:06.839 --> 01:28:08.925
Come on, you're this close!

01:28:09.155 --> 01:28:10.565
What's wrong?

01:28:10.781 --> 01:28:13.023
- Grab it, come on.
- Grab it, Peter!

01:28:14.368 --> 01:28:15.743
Come on, Jack.

01:28:16.829 --> 01:28:18.239
And one!

01:28:30.676 --> 01:28:32.585
Wait for the good pitches.

01:28:32.803 --> 01:28:34.629
Wait for the good pitches!

01:28:41.269 --> 01:28:43.022
Jack! Jack!
He's our man.

01:28:43.048 --> 01:28:45.291
If he can't do it, no one can!

01:28:46.941 --> 01:28:48.269
He's stealing second!

01:28:53.072 --> 01:28:54.732
No, now stop it!

01:28:54.991 --> 01:28:58.822
We're playing this game according to Master Jack's rules! Bad form!

01:28:59.078 --> 01:28:59.978
Sit down now!

01:29:00.004 --> 01:29:01.594
Let's resume the game!

01:29:01.789 --> 01:29:03.864
Very violent sport, isn't it, baseball?

01:29:08.962 --> 01:29:10.374
Come on, Jack!

01:29:11.006 --> 01:29:12.338
Run home, Jack!

01:29:12.364 --> 01:29:13.783
Run home, Jack!

01:29:21.266 --> 01:29:22.926
"Run home, Jack."

01:29:23.143 --> 01:29:24.669
Smee, no, no, no!

01:29:24.695 --> 01:29:27.117
They've got it backwards!

01:29:27.313 --> 01:29:28.973
Tell them to turn it around!

01:29:29.232 --> 01:29:30.477
Maggie?

01:29:31.234 --> 01:29:32.693
Switch!

01:29:37.657 --> 01:29:40.047
Home run, Jack!
Home run, Jack!

01:29:40.073 --> 01:29:41.382
Home run, Jack!

01:29:42.078 --> 01:29:44.615
Home run, Jack. Home run, Jack.

01:29:52.880 --> 01:29:54.789
He can't hit the curve.

01:30:20.323 --> 01:30:22.280
My Jack!

01:30:24.494 --> 01:30:25.608
My Jack.

01:30:34.921 --> 01:30:36.257
You did it!

01:30:36.283 --> 01:30:37.982
Hoist him up!

01:30:42.219 --> 01:30:43.778
That's my boy!

01:30:43.804 --> 01:30:45.695
You did it, son!

01:31:23.468 --> 01:31:24.499
Gotta fly!

01:31:25.386 --> 01:31:26.666
Happy thought.

01:31:26.929 --> 01:31:31.140
Happy thought, happy thought, happy thought, happy...

01:31:31.433 --> 01:31:33.841
One great, big happy thought!

01:31:34.269 --> 01:31:35.728
Less is more.

01:31:38.191 --> 01:31:39.471
I can!

01:33:10.905 --> 01:33:14.772
"Tootles. Wendy. John.

01:33:15.034 --> 01:33:17.607
Michael. Peter."

01:33:40.183 --> 01:33:41.402
Be careful, Peter.

01:33:41.428 --> 01:33:44.206
You're a lot taller than you used to be.

01:33:45.397 --> 01:33:47.105
Well, say something.

01:33:49.484 --> 01:33:51.275
Do you like my dress?

01:33:56.115 --> 01:33:57.858
You look beautiful.

01:34:03.331 --> 01:34:05.240
What's the occasion?

01:34:05.750 --> 01:34:06.913
You are.

01:34:07.960 --> 01:34:09.834
It's a welcome-home party.

01:34:15.759 --> 01:34:17.134
What happened here?

01:34:17.344 --> 01:34:18.624
Hook.

01:34:18.845 --> 01:34:20.719
Burnt it when you didn't come back.

01:34:41.617 --> 01:34:42.993
Kiss.

01:34:48.500 --> 01:34:49.875
Wendy.

01:34:53.212 --> 01:34:54.872
This is Wendy's house.

01:34:55.131 --> 01:34:57.170
Tootles and Nibs built it for her.

01:35:00.177 --> 01:35:01.802
I remember.

01:35:03.889 --> 01:35:05.597
Wendy would sit in that chair.

01:35:07.059 --> 01:35:08.518
But it wasn't there.

01:35:08.544 --> 01:35:09.492
It was here.

01:35:10.604 --> 01:35:14.222
We used to sit here while she'd darn socks and tell us stories.

01:35:15.484 --> 01:35:17.192
She slept here.

01:35:17.903 --> 01:35:19.860
Tink, your apartment was right here.

01:35:20.071 --> 01:35:21.316
Yes.

01:35:21.948 --> 01:35:25.946
Little Michael in his basket bed, right here.

01:35:26.870 --> 01:35:28.115
John.

01:35:36.254 --> 01:35:39.420
Teddy. My Teddy.

01:35:44.470 --> 01:35:47.636
Mother used to put him in the pram to keep me company.

01:35:53.271 --> 01:35:55.263
I remember my mother.

01:35:56.482 --> 01:35:58.273
I remember her.

01:36:00.569 --> 01:36:03.854
You can be sure, very fine schools indeed.

01:36:04.489 --> 01:36:08.273
First, he will attend Whitehall, then Oxford.

01:36:08.535 --> 01:36:09.449
And of course...

01:36:09.662 --> 01:36:14.656
...after graduation, he will prepare for a judgeship in the highest court...

01:36:14.917 --> 01:36:19.459
...making time for marriage and family and all of that.

01:36:19.671 --> 01:36:20.999
Just like his father.

01:36:21.256 --> 01:36:23.794
<i>Isn't that what grownups want for their children?</i>

01:36:24.050 --> 01:36:24.748
<i>I was afraid.</i>

01:36:24.774 --> 01:36:26.114
<i>I didn't wanna grow up.</i>

01:36:26.302 --> 01:36:29.338
<i>Everybody who grows up has to die someday.</i>

01:36:29.639 --> 01:36:31.431
<i>So I ran away.</i>

01:36:42.109 --> 01:36:43.354
<i>Tink...</i>

01:36:44.653 --> 01:36:46.860
<i>... you came and you saved me.</i>

01:36:47.531 --> 01:36:49.714
<i>You brought me to Never Land.</i>

01:36:49.740 --> 01:36:51.471
<i>You taught me to fly.</i>

01:36:54.246 --> 01:36:58.540
<i>But I was still a little boy, and I missed my mother.</i>

01:36:58.959 --> 01:37:02.292
<i>So I decided to fly home to my very own window.</i>

01:37:03.255 --> 01:37:04.120
<i>But it was shut.</i>

01:37:05.590 --> 01:37:06.965
<i>They'd forgotten about me.</i>

01:37:11.554 --> 01:37:16.466
<i>I found other windows to visit, ones that weren't shut closed on me.</i>

01:37:17.060 --> 01:37:18.438
<i>That's how I met Wendy.</i>

01:37:18.464 --> 01:37:20.620
<i>I chased my shadow in her nursery.</i>

01:37:20.814 --> 01:37:25.226
<i>I expected my shadow and I would join together like drops of water.</i>

01:37:35.745 --> 01:37:37.323
Boy!

01:37:40.041 --> 01:37:41.832
Why are you crying?

01:37:44.169 --> 01:37:45.794
What's your name?

01:37:46.964 --> 01:37:50.664
Wendy Moira Angela Darling.
What's yours?

01:37:51.051 --> 01:37:53.532
<i>I came back many times for Wendy.</i>

01:37:53.558 --> 01:37:55.288
<i>Always in the spring.</i>

01:37:58.058 --> 01:38:00.264
<i>And Wendy kept getting older...</i>

01:38:00.936 --> 01:38:01.967
<i>... and older.</i>

01:38:02.229 --> 01:38:06.096
<i>And then I came back the last time.</i>

01:38:06.399 --> 01:38:09.006
Peter, I can't come with you.

01:38:09.032 --> 01:38:11.549
I've forgotten how to fly.

01:38:12.655 --> 01:38:14.862
I'm old, Peter.

01:38:15.784 --> 01:38:18.191
Ever so much more than 20.

01:38:19.079 --> 01:38:21.652
- I grew up a long time ago.
- No, no, no!

01:38:21.873 --> 01:38:24.079
- You promised!
- I have children of my own now.

01:38:24.333 --> 01:38:26.824
They have children of their own.

01:38:27.044 --> 01:38:31.587
That's my grandchild, Moira, asleep in the bed.

01:38:31.840 --> 01:38:33.916
<i>When I saw her lying there sleeping...</i>

01:38:34.134 --> 01:38:37.171
<i>... at that moment, something changed in me forever.</i>

01:38:37.388 --> 01:38:39.464
I shall give her a kiss.

01:38:40.808 --> 01:38:44.058
No! No, Peter!
No buttons, no thimbles.

01:38:44.311 --> 01:38:48.640
I couldn't bear her heart to be broken when she finds she can't keep you.

01:38:51.151 --> 01:38:52.182
No.

01:38:53.903 --> 01:38:56.858
I mean a real kiss.

01:39:20.805 --> 01:39:23.889
I can see why you have trouble finding a happy thought.

01:39:25.351 --> 01:39:28.055
So many sad memories, Peter.

01:39:29.688 --> 01:39:31.396
Bye, Teddy.

01:39:33.442 --> 01:39:36.727
Not Teddy. Daddy!

01:39:37.529 --> 01:39:38.692
Daddy!

01:39:42.660 --> 01:39:44.533
Peter, you're a daddy.

01:39:48.498 --> 01:39:49.328
Hi, Jack.

01:39:49.541 --> 01:39:51.208
<i>I know why I came back.</i>

01:39:51.234 --> 01:39:52.899
<i>I know why I grew up.</i>

01:39:53.670 --> 01:39:56.623
<i>I wanted to be a father.</i>

01:39:57.089 --> 01:39:58.714
I'm a daddy.

01:40:01.094 --> 01:40:02.802
My happy thought.

01:40:03.722 --> 01:40:04.966
I got it!

01:40:05.181 --> 01:40:07.672
I got it! I found it!

01:40:10.102 --> 01:40:10.932
I lost it!

01:40:12.688 --> 01:40:15.393
Just hold that happy thought, Peter!

01:40:42.676 --> 01:40:44.336
Peter Pan!

01:41:11.579 --> 01:41:13.488
He's back! He's back!

01:41:13.706 --> 01:41:15.248
He's back!

01:42:09.677 --> 01:42:10.756
Play!

01:42:11.011 --> 01:42:12.589
Play!

01:42:40.581 --> 01:42:42.206
You are the Pan.

01:43:02.936 --> 01:43:07.016
You can fly, you can fight, and you can...

01:43:54.362 --> 01:43:55.772
Tink, you in there?

01:43:59.533 --> 01:44:00.696
Are you sad?

01:44:00.951 --> 01:44:02.990
No, I'm neither. Please go away.

01:44:03.203 --> 01:44:04.531
Oh, you're sick.

01:44:05.080 --> 01:44:06.016
You need a Band-Aid.

01:44:06.042 --> 01:44:06.931
Or a thermometer!

01:44:07.123 --> 01:44:09.697
That's how Nibs made the Wendy lady better.

01:44:09.918 --> 01:44:12.456
Oh, no, Peter! It's not about that!

01:44:12.671 --> 01:44:13.536
Yes, it is!

01:44:13.755 --> 01:44:16.425
Nibs put the thermometer in her mouth.

01:44:17.509 --> 01:44:18.920
Felt all better.

01:44:21.429 --> 01:44:23.256
Don't we have the greatest adventures?

01:44:25.141 --> 01:44:28.510
Do you remember your next great adventure to save your kids?

01:44:29.311 --> 01:44:30.805
Kids?

01:44:32.315 --> 01:44:34.058
Peter Pan's got kids?

01:44:35.360 --> 01:44:36.735
Why are you in Never Land?

01:44:36.944 --> 01:44:39.020
To always be a little boy and have fun.

01:44:39.238 --> 01:44:40.541
I like this game.

01:44:40.567 --> 01:44:42.098
Ask me another one.

01:44:56.547 --> 01:44:58.255
Oh, dear me! I did it.

01:44:58.507 --> 01:45:00.478
Tink, look what happened!

01:45:00.504 --> 01:45:02.316
You broke your house.

01:45:05.221 --> 01:45:06.799
You're humongous.

01:45:09.017 --> 01:45:11.887
This is the only wish I ever wished for myself.

01:45:13.354 --> 01:45:16.106
This is the biggest feeling I've ever, ever felt.

01:45:16.358 --> 01:45:21.268
And this is the first time I've been big enough to have it.

01:45:22.155 --> 01:45:25.654
Peter, I wanna give you a kiss.

01:45:29.286 --> 01:45:31.492
No, I mean a real kiss.

01:45:37.211 --> 01:45:39.204
I love you, Peter Pan.

01:45:39.880 --> 01:45:41.789
I love...

01:45:42.007 --> 01:45:42.837
...her.

01:45:43.050 --> 01:45:44.627
"Her," who?

01:45:45.552 --> 01:45:47.130
Mo...

01:45:47.387 --> 01:45:48.336
Moira!

01:45:48.764 --> 01:45:50.673
I love Moira...

01:45:51.683 --> 01:45:54.138
...and Jack and Maggie.

01:45:57.815 --> 01:45:59.225
Jack and Maggie...

01:46:04.946 --> 01:46:06.985
I have a plan. Tink?

01:46:08.283 --> 01:46:09.445
Come on. You gotta come.

01:46:11.118 --> 01:46:14.238
When it's all over, you'll leave and never come back again.

01:46:19.878 --> 01:46:21.787
What are you staring at, Peter?

01:46:23.047 --> 01:46:24.458
Save them.

01:46:25.091 --> 01:46:26.549
Go save them.

01:46:29.762 --> 01:46:31.007
You silly ass, go!

01:47:12.303 --> 01:47:16.596
Jack, it's a very special time when a pirate receives his first earring.

01:47:16.807 --> 01:47:21.932
It's like the first time you run someone through with your blade.

01:47:24.607 --> 01:47:25.437
Now, Jack...

01:47:25.649 --> 01:47:29.232
...I'm gonna ask you to bend your head ever so slightly.

01:47:29.486 --> 01:47:31.811
A little more. That's it.

01:47:32.072 --> 01:47:35.904
And brace yourself, lad.
Because this...

01:47:36.159 --> 01:47:38.566
...is really going to hurt.

01:47:47.546 --> 01:47:49.752
Smee, what is that?

01:48:00.766 --> 01:48:02.676
Who is that, captain?

01:48:06.647 --> 01:48:08.474
It's Peter Pan.

01:48:08.816 --> 01:48:11.272
Has it been three days?

01:48:11.861 --> 01:48:13.319
'Tis true, Peter...

01:48:13.571 --> 01:48:16.026
...time does fly.

01:48:17.783 --> 01:48:20.356
And so do you, I see.

01:48:20.785 --> 01:48:25.614
How did you ever manage to fit into those smashing tights again, Peter?

01:48:29.336 --> 01:48:32.123
Hand over my son now and you and your men may go free.

01:48:32.464 --> 01:48:35.141
Why don't you ask the lad yourself?

01:48:35.167 --> 01:48:37.613
Jack, someone to see you, son.

01:48:41.347 --> 01:48:42.929
Jack, give me your hand.

01:48:42.955 --> 01:48:44.208
We're going home.

01:48:44.476 --> 01:48:46.018
I am home.

01:48:47.187 --> 01:48:48.515
Good form!

01:48:49.022 --> 01:48:51.312
You see, Peter, he is my son.

01:48:51.338 --> 01:48:52.996
He loves me dearly.

01:48:53.234 --> 01:48:56.354
And I'm prepared to fight dearly for him.

01:48:56.570 --> 01:49:00.022
I've waited long to shake your hand with this.

01:49:00.282 --> 01:49:02.951
Peter Pan, prepare to meet thy doom!

01:49:03.952 --> 01:49:06.076
Dark and sinister man, have at thee.

01:49:37.443 --> 01:49:39.187
Don't you love it, laddie?

01:49:39.213 --> 01:49:42.095
Once you've shed blood, it's hard to stop!

01:49:42.323 --> 01:49:44.648
It's a pirate's life, my lad!

01:49:44.909 --> 01:49:46.736
Jack, Jack!

01:49:47.120 --> 01:49:48.132
Don't I know him?

01:49:48.158 --> 01:49:50.478
No, you've never seen him before!

01:49:52.250 --> 01:49:55.250
You won't believe this, but I found my happy thought.

01:49:55.461 --> 01:49:58.545
It took me three days, then guess what happened?

01:49:58.756 --> 01:50:00.380
Up I went!

01:50:00.591 --> 01:50:02.797
You know what my happy thought was?

01:50:07.222 --> 01:50:08.847
It was you.

01:50:18.733 --> 01:50:22.316
That's my dad... but he hates to fly!

01:50:22.529 --> 01:50:24.604
Bangerang!

01:51:04.319 --> 01:51:05.513
Call out the militia!

01:51:05.539 --> 01:51:07.131
We'll need every last man!

01:51:15.789 --> 01:51:20.700
If there's anybody not fighting, get here quick!

01:51:29.635 --> 01:51:31.628
Form ranks!

01:51:31.930 --> 01:51:34.966
Form ranks!

01:51:35.850 --> 01:51:38.471
Show them the white light we're made of!

01:51:38.686 --> 01:51:41.806
Remember the fires from hell that forged you!

01:51:42.022 --> 01:51:44.015
Charge!

01:51:45.901 --> 01:51:47.478
Now!

01:51:51.906 --> 01:51:55.193
We'll show you who's chicken!
Watch this!

01:52:18.433 --> 01:52:21.054
Smee! Do something intelligent!

01:52:23.438 --> 01:52:26.272
"Smee, Smee"!
 What about Smee?

01:52:28.859 --> 01:52:30.437
What about Smee?

01:52:31.445 --> 01:52:32.524
What about me?

01:52:40.538 --> 01:52:41.996
Thud ball!

01:52:54.092 --> 01:52:55.337
Fire!

01:53:06.521 --> 01:53:09.012
Hey, wait!

01:53:09.899 --> 01:53:11.014
Look out below!

01:53:17.991 --> 01:53:21.194
Somebody help!

01:53:31.587 --> 01:53:32.236
Here we go.

01:53:32.262 --> 01:53:33.853
Take it, take it, take it!

01:53:34.548 --> 01:53:36.754
Lost Boys, down!

01:53:43.265 --> 01:53:44.973
My eyes!

01:53:45.309 --> 01:53:48.642
It's time for Smee.

01:53:58.363 --> 01:54:00.027
Where do you think you're going?

01:54:00.053 --> 01:54:01.508
Get away from that window!

01:54:12.209 --> 01:54:13.372
Hook!

01:54:17.214 --> 01:54:19.753
Rufio.

01:54:23.346 --> 01:54:25.137
The old man is mine.

01:54:25.556 --> 01:54:29.090
Jack! Save me!

01:54:29.309 --> 01:54:30.851
Maggie!

01:54:41.530 --> 01:54:43.273
Get down here!

01:54:44.157 --> 01:54:45.568
Maggie!

01:54:45.784 --> 01:54:47.361
Daddy!

01:54:49.412 --> 01:54:50.823
Wait, ain't you...

01:54:51.080 --> 01:54:52.456
Peter Pan.

01:55:02.926 --> 01:55:04.254
Daddy!

01:55:04.510 --> 01:55:06.218
Daddy?

01:55:08.806 --> 01:55:12.886
Peter Pan's my dad?

01:55:32.287 --> 01:55:34.363
I'll never lose you again.

01:55:37.250 --> 01:55:40.204
